FBIS3-36590 "drsov026_n_94001" FBIS-SOV-94-026 Document Type:Daily Report 8 Feb 1994 Turkmenistan President in `Good Condition' After Surgery in U.S. LD0702130994 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1143 GMT 7 Feb 94 LD0702130994 Moscow INTERFAX Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Turkmenistan President Saparmurad Niyazov had surgery in Houston, Texas, U.S.A., Saturday [5 February], for phlebitis of his left leg. He flew to the U.S. for an examination on February 1 following the end of the World Economic Forum in Davos, Switzerland. Sources close to the Turkmenistan Government told Interfax that Niyazov was in good condition after the surgery. He is expected in Turkmenistan next Wednesday or Thursday.
